4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under the Solid Wastes and Recyclable Materials
6 Management Act, the Alabama Department of Environmental
7 Management is authorized to adopt rules to provide for
8 the disposal and reuse of solid wastes.
9 This bill would require the department to adopt
10 rules providing for the beneficial reuse of foundry
11 sand.
12 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
13 technical revisions to update the existing code
14 language to current style.
15
16
17 A BILL
18 TO BE ENTITLED
19 AN ACT
20
21 Relating to recycling; to amend Section 22-27-12, Code
22 of Alabama 1975, to require the Alabama Department of
23 Environmental Management to adopt rules providing for the
24 beneficial reuse of foundry sand; and to make nonsubstantive,
25 technical revisions to update the existing code language to
26 current style..
27 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
28 Section 1. Section 22-27-12, Code of Alabama 1975, is
