Section 1. Section 22-27-12, Code of Alabama 1975, is
HB176 INTRODUCED
29 amended to read as follows:
30 "§22-27-12
31 (a) The department may do the following:
32 (1) Adopt rules to implement this article.
33 (2)a. Adopt rules establishing requirements and
34 restrictions for the management of solid waste, excluding the
35 collection and transportation of nonhazardous and nonmedical
36 solid waste.
37 b. The rules may include factors such as the
38 characteristics of the solid waste, the potential for
39 contamination of soils or ground and surface waters, the
40 design and operation of management facilities, the financial
41 capabilities of the applicant, soil and geological
42 considerations, human health, and other environmental
43 considerations.
44 c. With respect to solid waste disposal or materials
45 recovery facilities, the rules may also include factors such
46 as the quantity, nature, and origin of solid wastes and
47 recovered materials to be managed.
48 (3) The department may condition Condition the issuance
49 of a permit for any solid waste management or materials
50 recovery facility upon the facility being consistent with
51 applicable rules as are necessary to carry out the intent of
52 this article and the department's responsibilities under this
53 article. Permits shall be issued for a period of time based on
54 design life of the a facility and may include renewal periods
55 as determined by rules and not inconsistent with federal law.
56 (3)(4) Issue permits, notices, and orders, specify the
