105 (b)(1) Not later than January 1, 2027, the department
106 shall adopt rules that provide for the beneficial reuse of
107 foundry sand. The rules shall provide that foundry sand may be
108 used as any of the following:
109 a. Raw material in the manufacture of asphalt, cement,
110 and concrete products.
111 b. Subbase for hard-surface road construction.
112 c. Fill Material.
Page 4

c. Fill Material.
HB176 INTRODUCED
113 d. Filler for sandbags used for emergency flood
114 control.
115 e. Leachate control drainage material at sanitary
116 landfills.
117 f. Alternative cover material at sanitary landfills.
118 (2) For purposes of this subsection, the term "foundry
119 sand" means a solid by-product from the foundry industry that
120 is derived from molding, core-making, and casting cleaning
121 processes that primarily contains sand, olivine, or clay and
122 this is suitable for disposal as a solid waste in a sanitary
123 landfill."
124 Section 2. This act shall become effective on June 1,
125 2026.
